# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project following the official Vercel documentation.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 using npm
- Updated `package.json` to include the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the complete dependency tree

### 2. Analytics Integration
**Modified:** `pages/_app.js`
- Added import for Analytics component from `@vercel/analytics/next`
- Integrated the `<Analytics />` component following Next.js Pages Router pattern
- Wrapped the existing Component with a React fragment to include Analytics alongside the page content

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Web Analytics quickstart guide for Next.js Pages Router:
- Fetched the latest documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
- Used the framework-specific integration for Next.js Pages Router
- Placed the Analytics component in the root `_app.js` file to track all pages

### Code Changes
```javascript
// Before
import '../styles/globals.css'

export default function App({ Component, pageProps }) {
  return <Component {...pageProps} />
}

// After
import '../styles/globals.css'
import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next'

export default function App({ Component, pageProps }) {
  return (
    <>
      <Component {...pageProps} />
      <Analytics />
    </>
  )
}
```

## Verification

✅ Package installed successfully (@vercel/analytics@2.0.1)
✅ JavaScript syntax validated
✅ Code follows Next.js Pages Router best practices
✅ Lock file updated with all dependencies
✅ All changes staged for commit

## Next Steps

After deployment to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics section)
2. Deploy the application
3. Verify Analytics is working by checking the Network tab for requests to `/<unique-path>/view`
4. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard

## Notes

- The Analytics component will automatically track page views across all pages in the application
- No additional configuration is needed for basic analytics tracking
- The component works in both development and production environments
- Build failure encountered was due to missing Supabase environment variables (pre-existing issue, unrelated to Analytics implementation)
